definition.value: Anatomical structure composed of skeletogenic mesenchyme cells that have fused to form a single syncytial network.
Subpopulation of skeletogenic mesenchyme forming a chain on the oral (i.e. ventral) side of the embryo.
Subpopulation of skeletogenic mesenchyme forming a chain on the aboral (i.e. dorsal) side of the embryo.
Subpopulation of skeletogenic mesenchyme forming a cluster (i.e. a group of cells) in the ventrolateral region of the embryo.
Subpopulation of skeletogenic mesenchyme forming a chain on either side of the developing digestive tract, along the blastocoel wall and towards the animal pole.

label.value: right lateral chain of skeletogenic mesenchyme

definition.value: Subpopulation of skeletogenic mesenchyme forming a chain along the blastocoel wall towards the animal pole on the right side of the embryo.

label.value: left lateral chain of skeletogenic mesenchyme

definition.value: Subpopulation of skeletogenic mesenchyme forming a chain along the blastocoel wall towards the animal pole on the left side of the embryo.
